	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Aug 29th 7:00 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[1.75]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Everything Calabar suggested is good, but I'd like to point out a few things.<br><br>For the back item, you could buy a Molten Cloak, which is +4 AC +4 INT +4 WIS, it's cheaper than Mammoth Hide but less common.<br><br>For primary hand, you could get one of these:<br>Velium Etched Stone Mace<br>Spirit Tome<br>Dark Ember<br>Sharkbone Warhammer (which is what I'm using)<br>Paw of Oppola (spelling)<br><br>For rings, you could buy Velium Jasper Rings, which are +7 WIS.&nbsp;&nbsp;Not that much, but a little better than Platinum.<br><br>For the belt, crystalline is fine, but 500pp is a rip-off (I think) I bought mine for 175pp, and with the bazaar they are much cheaper.<br><br>Black Alloy Medallion, for the neck slot, is a good choice, but with the recent additions of focus effects, it will now cost 800-1kpp.  Which I think is ridiculous, considering the difficulty to get it, and how common it is.  You can get the Black Iron Medallion (2 less WIS, no focus effect) for about 50pp.<br><br>For arms, when you gather enough money (which I never will), you can buy Nathsar Vambraces (those purple ones you see all the high level druids wear).  I'm not sure of the WIS but it is better than 3.  For now, Giant Scalemail is fine.<br><br>For chest, I highly recommend replacing the Chitin Protector, which, in my opinion, is a waste except for looks.  Buy a Foreman's Tunic (50-150pp), or Shroud of Nature (800-1kpp, but I got lucky and bought one for 400pp).<br><br>For non GEB feet (overpriced, since the bazaar, in my opinion), it depends on your race.  For wood elf, half elf, and humans worshipping Tunare, buy Mithril Reinforced Boots (250pp, +7 AC +2 WIS +2 CHA).  For halflings, do the Acolyte's Anklet quest.  For non-halfling Karana worshippers, I don't really know, but I've heard of an armor called Vale Studded.<br><br>For Othmir Fur Cap, look for tailors who will sell these at a reduced price (I bought one for 185pp, and the next day saw them for sale for even cheaper).<br><br>For the Velium Ruby Veil, I think Calabar meant 500Pp-1kpp, not 500gp :)  I bought mine for 300pp from a high level druid.<br><br>That should do it, and bring you over 200 WIS (unless you seriously screwed up with your starting points).<br>&nbsp;<br>Ganerin, level 39 Wood Elf Druid<br>Vinaelil, level 25 Dark Elf Warrior<br><br>Officer of the Rune of Flames guild on the Veeshan Server</td></tr>
