	   <a name=103063453429817></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f103063453429817><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=8&mid=103063453429817>RE: equipment</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=8&mid=103063453429817#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=117530><span id=Guru>Calabar</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>193 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Aug 29th 11:35 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I’ll do my best at suggesting a few things, but gear upgrades are not my strong suit.&nbsp;&nbsp;*grins*  And I would also like to make an observation.  There seems to be about three levels of wisdom gear for druids: low, medium and high.  The low-end stuff is great when you hit your late teens and decide to become a true caster.  You can get a fair amount of wisdom by buying the low end items and make due until you have the funds to buy better items.  The mid range items are about where you and I are at.  These items tend to run a few hundred plats each or you can try to earn them yourself.  Then there is the high-end stuff that tends to cost over 1k plat each.  This is the stuff that is too high level to get yet and most of us just drool over them unless we have some way of tweaking our characters.  Thanks to making cheese when it first came out, I was able to afford a few of the high-end items, but there are still a lot of things I’m drooling over.<br><br><b>Ears</b> – Forest Loops  <br>This is about as good as it gets until you have a lot of plats to spend.<br><br><b>Head</b> – Savants Cap<br>Othmir Fur Cap - +6 wis and several other stats.  This should run you about 3 to 4 hundred pp.<br><br><b>Face</b> – Platinum Ruby Veil<br>Velium Ruby Veil - +8 str and +8 wis.  I think this generally runs between 500gp and 1kpp.<br><br><b>Shoulders</b> – Braided Ivy Cords<br>These are good to stick with until you can afford the higher end items or you do the Coldain Prayer Shawl quest.  If you like to do trade skills, I’d recommend the shall quest.  The last two shawls give manna regeneration.  If you want to check it out, go to EQTraders.com and look under quests.  <br><br><b>Chest</b> – Brown Chitin Protector<br>You could buy a Foreman Tunic with +3 str and +3 wis for a couple hundred plats.  Or you should buy a Shroud of Nature that will give you +6 wis for around 800pp.  I’m trying to save money for an Acrylia Studded Tunic with +11 AC +8 Str +12 Dex +8 Wis that is player made and sells for about 2k.<br><br><b>Arms</b> – Giant Scale Mail Sleeves<br>Platinum Armbands will give you +3 str and +3 wis.  I’m not sure how much they run, but I’d guess in the low hundreds.  On the higher end are the Elder Spiritists Vambraces.  These arms have no wisdom bonus, which is stupid as they are druid only, but they do have a clickable effect of Drones of Doom.  But you have to be level 45 to use them and they run about 2kpp. I have a pair waiting for me in the bank.  <br><br><b>Wrist</b> – Runed Mithril Bracers<br>Again, these are good until you can afford the high-end items.  These are better than the Chipped Bone Bracelets that I’m using.   <br><br><b>Hands</b> – Gnome Skin Gloves<br>Sad to say, but you have about the best wisdom gloves you can get without spending a fortune.  And as a nice side benefit, black goes with just about everything.<br><br><b>Legs</b> – Rawhide<br>Obviously, you can do better.  I’d suggest Gatorscale Leggings with +4 wisdom.  They should run you about 400pp or you can camp the ancient crock in upper Guk for a pair.  The arms drop more often, but you could get lucky.  <br><br><b>Feet</b> - NA<br>You could try for a pair of Crystal Lined Slippers that give +3 wis.  They should run about four or five hundred plat.  Or you could try to get a pair from the Crystal Caverns.  I used my cheese money to buy a pair of Golden Efreeti Boots with +9 wisdom.  Unfortunately, they tend to run from 3 to 4k.<br><br><b>Neck</b> – Black Alloy Medallion<br>This is a good item until you can afford something really expensive.  However, you might also look into doing the Warden Symbol of Tunare quest.  This item has +3 wis but also has a free clickable root spell.  But I’ll warn you, it can be very time consuming. I’ve been trying to finish it for ten levels now.<br><br><b>Waist</b> – Strawspun Belt<br>I’m using a Crystalline Belt with +3 wis.  I think it runs around 500pp.  You can get this item from the Crystal Caverns too.<br><br><b>Fingers</b> – Platinum Jasper Rings<br>These are great until you can afford higher end rings.  I only have one so far. I really need to take the time to buy another one.<br><br><b>Back</b><br>I would recommend a Mammoth Hide Cloak with +4 wis.  I think they run about 600pp.  Or you can camp the Ice Goblin Alchemist in Permafrost for it.  Thanks to that wonderful cheese money I was able to buy an Acrylia Studded Cloak with +10 wis that is player made and sells for about 2k.<br><br><b>Range Slot</b><br>For now you can get a Small Wisdom Deity for a couple hundred plats.  But if you do the shawl quest you’ll get a +3 wisdom item for the ranged slot with your third shawl.  <br><br><b>Primary Hand</b><br>Paw of Opolla with +9 wisdom and some other good stats.  You can buy this item for about 1k or do what I did and quest for it yourself.  It’s a great item and I like it all the more for having earned it myself.<br><br><b>Secondary Hand</b><br>Testament of Vanear, which is +10 wisdom.  This is a relatively easy item to get.  It’s just a mater of finding the mob to kill, which is on a very long respawn timer.  It’s Secondary Melee only, so you can’t use a shield with it, but its still a great item.<br><br><br>By buying these items you will be giving up armor class for wisdom, but as I’m sure you know by your level, druids are better at casting than melee anyway.  We can still melee of course, which I often do when soloing, but it’s a bad idea to do it in groups.  With a good manna pool we can be much more useful in a group as casters.<br><br>As I’ve recommended many times on this board, you should spend some time in the Bazaar.  Sort the items by class and wisdom and watch the prices for a while to get a feel for what things are going for on your server.  You can often get very good deals from people who are simply trying to dump items out of their banks.  <br><br>Best of luck,<br><br>&nbsp;<br><b>Pait Spiritwalker</b><br>Vah Shir Shaman, 55th Season<br><b>Namir Shadowstalker</b><br>Wood Elf Ranger, 51st Season<br><b>Calabar Silverthorn</b><br>Wood Elf Druid, 51st Season<br><br><b>Seventh Hammer</b> </td></tr>
